caption: We had the Holy burger, Tenders, sweet potato tots, and the chicken sliders. Everything was good expect the tenders which looked a bit burnt and a bit to dry. The price wasn't too expensive and is a place I'd come back if I was in the area again. One thing we noticed while we we were waiting to pick up the food was that the place needed a little TLC...the floors looked and felt a little sticky and the walls also needed a cleaning

Me and friends came here all the way from Long Island because the elmont location was closed. We ordered 6 spicy chicken sliders  and 3 drinks. Let’s start off with the drinks. They charged us 2 dollars for a fountain soda. We thought that was ok. Until we saw them poured it in. The size of the cup was smaller then kids cup size at chunky cheeses . Only 6 oz to be exact. Next we go to the sliders. The chicken was super dry and barely any spicy sauce. Very disappointed with this location. Please support the location in elmont which actually makes fire sliders. Avoid this location !!!!!!!!
Literally the best fast food spot l ever eaten at.

The burger and sweet potato fries are excellent, the Impossible Burger is fine (nothing wrong with it -- just not my cup of tea), and the tots are just okay.  Service is quick and the burger really is quite delectable, even if not everything meets that standard.  Recommended!

If you want to eat 100% halal fast food, you gotta try this place!!! It's very difficult to find places which are actually 100%. 😋💯 I was really looking forward to this place, that I wanted to order off their secret menu, but this location doesn't have that, I ordered  couple of things, the holy burger was good but really needed more flavor, cheese fries were good, chicken tenders a bit over cooked but were ok , this place also has impossible meat for those looking to eat vegetarian. Even though it was a small store we were able to still eat in, I hope they can grow and get more workers at the place.

At the first moment  you come to this restaurant  team give you an excellent feeling. Very hospitable waiters, it is a happy restaurant to go out with buddies or with your date. Great  cuisine, specialist  chef de cuisine, comfortable  cost and attentive  service. Highly recommended.

I went in after work while heading to a show down the street. I ordered fries and a burger (without lettuce, just not a fan). The place had a small crowd that apparently knew the guy behind the counter, nice dude. After 5-7min (wasn't counting, just kinda felt it) my food came out. The burger was pretty good. Exactly what I wanted, but, admittedly, it's exactly what I expected (and wanted). The fries, though, were an exception. They were delicious. They had what appeared to be a light breading, and, by my god or yours, they were exceptional. Hot,incredibly crispy,and not over salted, as is the case with many places. 5/5 I will be eating there again.

Honestly I wouldn't advise anybody to eat there. The place is very small and gets crowded within minutes. Then the food... Fries were cold. I ordered a holy burger. The patty was dry, and worst of all the "brioche" ban was like plastic. It would slip away from the burger and stick to your teeth, making it tough to cut it even when you bite quite hard. Finally, the coke was nothing like a coke. It was more like seltzer water - yes I'm serious. All that for $17... There was a group of friends eating at the table next to me who were only taking pictures for fun. I could see they weren't impressed either. And before getting my order served I heard one of them say how the coke was bad. Those who say this place is good have never eaten a real burger I'm afraid.

The chicken consisted of 2 cutlets of grilled white meat (not breaded), unlike the fast food joints. The sauce is pretty good all over it.

I would definitely recommend this spot to anyone is in the area they do shakes as well strawberry chocolate and pistachio flavored.  Check them out you will not be disappointed.

Seating area is newly renovated and nice.
